const personalImageAlt = "Cristian Pulido";
---

<article
  class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-8 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 md:flex-row"
>
  <div
    class="[&>p]:mb-4 [&>p>strong]:text-yellow-500 dark:[&>p>strong]:text-yellow-100 [&>p>strong]:font-normal [&>p>strong]:font-mono text-pretty order-2 md:order-1"
  >
    <p>
      Hello! I'm Cristian Pulido, a passionate application developer currently working at 
      <strong>Hospital Virgen del Rocío in Seville</strong>, where I develop medical software 
      solutions to improve healthcare processes and patient care. I completed my higher degree 
      in Application Development at Salesianos de Triana (Seville), gaining solid technical 
      and practical training in programming and software development.
    </p>

    <p>
      With over <strong>one year of professional experience</strong>, I have mastered 
      technologies including <strong>TypeScript, JavaScript, React, Next.js, Java, 
      Spring Boot, Docker, Tailwind CSS, HTML, CSS, SQL and NoSQL Databases, Node.js, 
      and Express</strong>. I continuously expand my skill set to stay current with 
      modern development practices and emerging technologies.
    </p>

    <p>
      As a software developer, <strong>I have developed various projects ranging from 
      e-commerce platforms to medical software</strong>, all visible on my GitHub. 
      My professional experience includes creating robust, scalable applications that 
      solve real-world problems in both commercial and healthcare environments.
    </p>
  </div>

  <img
    width="200"
    height="200"
    src="me.png"
    alt={personalImageAlt}
    class="order-1 object-cover w-64 h-full p-1 md:order-2 rotate-3 lg:p-2 lg:w-64 aspect-square rounded-2xl bg-black/20 dark:bg-yellow-500/5 ring-1 ring-black/70 dark:ring-white/20"
    style="object-position: 50% 50%"
  />
</article>

